<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--CocaineClergy     10-22 0170</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Cocaine Clergy,0173</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Priest, 77, Sentenced For Cocaine Smuggling</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GENEVA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 77-year-old Brazilian priest caught carrying 20
pounds of cocaine into Switzerland was convicted and sentenced to
eight years in prison for breaking narcotics laws.
   A Geneva jury court Friday sentenced three Brazilian
co-defendants to jail terms of up to 15 years for membership in a
ring smuggling the drug from Brazil to Milan, Italy.
   The Rev. Lino Christ, a Roman Catholic parish priest in Rio de
Janeiro, admitted he frequently traveled to Geneva to raise funds
for charity.
   But a co-defendant implicated him in the ring, where couriers
were rewarded with $10,000 a trip. Christ shared an apartment with
a mistress in Rio's plush Copacabana district, the court was told.
   ``All Brazilian priests have a little business on the side,''
Christ testified in court, but he did not elaborate.
   He was arrested in December after Geneva airport customs
officials seized cocaine with a street value of $1.8 million hidden
under a false bottom of his suitcase.
</TEXT>
