<HEAD>Malaysian Looking To Indonesia For A Rhino Mate</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Malaysia is looking for a country
willing to loan it a male Sumatran rhinoceros so it can mate the
rare species with its seven females, wildlife officials said today.
   Malaysia's only male Sumatran rhino still has not reached
maturity, said environment minister Law Hieng Ding.
   The rhinos would be bred at the Ayer Keroh Zoo in Malacca, 90
miles south of here and the Sungai Dusun Wildlife Reserve in
Selangor, about 30 miles from here.
