<1ST_LINE>u a BC-FairShooting     10-22 0176</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Fair Shooting,0184</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>One Dead, At Least Six Wounded In State Fair Shooting Spree</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman opened fire on the State Fair of Texas
midway late Friday, killing a man, wounding a policeman and causing
injuries to eight other people, authorities said.
   The shooting began between 11:15 and 11:30 p.m. just outside the
Cotton Bowl and ended around 12:20 a.m., police said.
   Police said they had several people in custody who fit the
gunman's description.
   A man taken to Baylor Medical Center was dead, said charge nurse
Debbie Mecham.
   A 37-year-old police officer, listed on a hospital log as Manuel
Vasquez, was in stable condition, Ms. Meacham said. The officer was
shot in the hand, authorities said.
   The hospital treated six other people who were hurt as they fell
or were trampled by the fleeing crowd, she said.
   In addition, three women who fled the shooting went into labor,
Ms. Mecham said.
   Two other injured fairgoers were taken to Parkland Memorial
Hospital, said a paramedic who refused to give a name.
</TEXT>
