<HEAD>Associated Press Managing Editors Elect 1989 Officers, Directors</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Paul Janensch of The Journal News in Rockland
County, N.Y., was elected president of The Associated Press
Managing Editors at the organization's annual meeting.
   The other new officers elected Friday were: Vice President Gene
Foreman of The Philadelphia Inquirer; Secretary Ralph Langer of The
Dallas Morning News, and Treasurer Alf Goodykoontz of the Richmond
Times-Dispatch and The Richmond News Leader.
   Named to posts by the executive committee were the chairman of
the Continuing Studies Committee, Sue Reisinger of The Miami News,
and, as vice chairman, Robert W. Ritter, who joins The Denver Post
on Nov. 7 from the San Bernardino County (Calif.) Sun.
   Elected to the APME Board of Directors for three-year terms were
incumbents: Beverly Kees of The Fresno (Calif.) Bee; Jack Keith of
The Bellingham (Wash.) Herald; Michael R. Fancher of The Seattle
Times; Michael E. Waller of The Hartford Courant, and Myrtle Barnes
of the Newport News (Va.) Daily Press@Times-Herald.
   Elected directors were: Robert McGruder of the Detroit Free
Press; Reid MacCluggage of The Day of New London, Conn., and Kathy
Kozdemba of The News-Leader, in Springfield, Mo.
