<2ND_LINE>PM-Bangladesh,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>10 Dead In Storm, 700 Missing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A storm packing 75 mph winds and
15-foot waves has left at least 10 people drowned and another 700
missing, authorities in Bangladesh said today.
   Residents said they had no warning of the storm that developed
suddenly in the Bay of Bengal.
   Rescue workers today found nine bodies floating in the bay near
the island of Maheskhali. One person also died in Dhaka, where more
than 1,000 were injured, officials said.
   At least 1,500 people had been reported missing Friday, but
district officials said today that about 800 were rescued.
Authorities said their search was continuing for the other 700,
most of them fishermen.
   The storm struck almost two months after floods inundated much
of Bangladesh, killing at least 1,000 people and leaving homeless
about 50 million of this impoverished country's 110 million people.
