<HEAD>Police Seize 96 Pounds Of Heroin In Australia's Biggest Drug Bust</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SYDNEY, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police said today they found nearly 100
pounds of heroin in the water tanks of a yacht and broke up a Hong
Kong-based drug ring by employing police officers as crew members.
Authorities said it was Australia's biggest heroin bust.
   In simultaneous raids overnight Friday, police arrested 21
people in Sydney and Hong Kong and seized 96 pounds of high-grade
Thai heroin with an estimated street value of $40 million.
   Seven people were arrested in Sydney and 14 others in raids on
60 premises in Hong Kong, Detective Inspector Cliff Foster said.
   In the ruse, two police officers were able to get jobs as crew
members aboard a 50-foot ketch that authorities suspected was being
used to ferry drugs, said Detective Inspector Mike Howard of the
Royal Hong Kong Police Force Drug Squad.
   Foster said the probe began in June after authorities were
tipped off that a large quantity of heroin was en route from Hong
Kong to Australia.
