<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``We all screamed, there was a bang and the boat began to tilt
... I said a prayer.'' _ Kirsty Spurling, a 14-year-old girl,
describing how she and her friends reacted when an Italian
freighter collided with a Greek cruise ship carrying hundreds of
youngsters.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``To abolish the right to silence is to place a terrible risk
against those who are verbally inadequate, those who are afraid,
who are simply cautious.'' _ Labor Party deputy leader Roy
Hattersley, on the British government's decision to end a suspect's
right to remain silent under police interrogation, comparable to
the U.S. Constitution's Fifth Amendment.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``It's the kitten in the tree syndrome. If a kitten gets caught,
everybody gathers around to rescue it,'' _ Patricia Warhol,
director of the American Cetacean Society in San Pedro, Calif.,
discussing the attention that the efforts to free three whales
trapped in Arctic ice has attracted around the world.
