<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0452</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rain, Snow Fall in Northeast; Gusty Winds Whip Through Parts of
West</HEAD>
<HEAD>By The Associated Press</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Rain and snow fell in the Northeast today, raising the risk of
flooding in some areas because of fallen leaves clogging drains,
and gusty winds whipped through parts of the West.
   Nearly 3 inches of rain Friday night near Trenton, N.J., caused
Assunpink Creek to rise a half-foot below flood stage. But by early
this morning it crested and started to recede slowly.
   Wet snow in the Catskills of eastern New York state left 3
inches on the ground at Slide Mountain. Wet snow also descended on
parts of western and central New York state, and about an inch fell
in several Vermont towns, leaving some roads slippery.
   Strong winds blew through parts of Montana and Wyoming this
morning, with Great Falls, Mont., registering a gust of 43 mph, and
parts of the Flathead Valley of Montana up to 49 mph.
   Showers were scattered in the lower Ohio Valley, lower Michigan,
and the lower Great Lakes.
   Today's forecast called for rain and wind in New England, the
Middle Atlantic States, and the upper Ohio Valley; scattered
showers in north-central Montana and southwest Texas; and gusty
winds from the northern Rockies to western Nebraska and South
Dakota.
   High temperatures were predicted in the 40s from much of New
England to the northern Appalachians and the upper Great Lakes, 50s
and 60s from the middle Atlantic Coast to the central and southern
Appalachians, lower Ohio Valley, middle and upper Mississippi
Valley, northern Plains, northern Rockies, and Pacific Northwest;
80s in southern Florida, southern and central Texas; 85 to 95 in
the desert Southwest and California's inland valleys; and in the
70s in the rest of the nation.
   Temperatures at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 23 degrees at
International Falls, Minn., to 78 at Phoenix and the Key West,
Fla., Naval Air Station.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 48 fair; Boston 50 rain; Buffalo 40 rain;
Charleston, S.C. 54 fair; Cincinnati 47 rain; Cleveland 45 drizzle;
Detroit 46 foggy; Miami 73 fair; New York 52 rain; Pittsburgh 43
cloudy; Portland, Maine 46 cloudy; Washington 46 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 42 fair; Chicago 42 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
57 fair; Denver 46 fair; Des Moines 35 partly cloudy; Indianapolis
44 fair; Kansas City 43 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 33 fair;
Nashville 50 fair; New Orleans 62 fair; St. Louis 46 partly cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 55 fair; Las Vegas 66 fair; Los Angeles 62
foggy; Phoenix 78 fair; Salt Lake City 51 fair; San Diego 66
cloudy; San Francisco 52 fair; Seattle 53 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 39 rain; Toronto 41 rain.
</TEXT>
