<HEAD>Student Taken Into Custody After Pipe Bomb Blasts Restroom</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEWBURY PARK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A student was taken into custody
after a pipe bomb exploded in a high school restroom and four other
bombs were found in lockers, authorities said.
   No one was hurt in the blast Friday but the boys' restroom was
extensively damaged, said Ventura County Sheriff's Sgt. Will Howe.
   The student, not identified because of his age, led deputies to
the other bombs after students and school officials said he might
be involved, Howe said.
   Most students at Newbury Park High School were attending a
homecoming rally when the explosion occurred and were not near the
restroom, Howe said.
   Principal Florence Lawyer said she had no idea why the bombs
were planted, but believes it was an isolated incident.
   Students were sent home after the blast.
