<HEAD>Man Shot In Face Walks More Than Mile To Police Department</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILWAUKEE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who was shot in the face walked eight
blocks to a police station to get help, authorities said.
   David Dixon, 46, was calm when he walked into the station
shortly after 9 p.m. Friday. ``He walked in and said someone shot
him,'' said the officer who was monitoring the door at the time.
   The officer, who asked not to be identified, said he called an
