<HEAD>Man Attacked By Kangaroo</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MELBOURNE, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man required 30 stitches after
being attacked by a kangaroo at a popular camping area. ``I believe
it was capable of killing,'' the victim said Saturday.
   Shaun Fitzpatrick, 36, said the kangaroo pounced on him Friday
while he fed bread to about five of the marsupials at Grampians
National Park in Victoria.
   A witness with a videocamera filmed the attack, which appeared
unprovoked.
   The gray male kangaroo jumped at Fitzpatrick and kicked and
clawed him. The animal scratched Fitzpatrick's face and caused a
groin wound that required stitches.
   Fitzpatrick's four children, brother, sister-in-law, and a
cousin visiting from England were with him but fled to their car
when the attack began.
