<HEAD>Bus Crash Kills Two West Germans</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: LEADS with 5 grafs to UPDATE with second death. Pick up last,
`The Civil...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>FIGUERAS, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A West German tourist bus veered off a
highway Saturday and overturned, killing two elderly West Germans
and injuring 21 other people, a Civil Guard traffic official said.
   The bus crashed at about 7 a.m. on the A-7 Mediterranean
highway, about nine miles south of this northeastern city, the
official said.
   The official identified the dead as the 73-year-old woman Luise
Jeschonneck and Friedrich Wilhelm Giunchi, 77, both of Duesseldorf.
He said the injured were from several other cities in West Germany,
but did not elaborate.
   The cause of the accident was not immediately known, he said.
   Hospital officials said 18 of the injured were treated and
released, and three remained hospitalized with broken bones.
   The Civil Guard official said it was not known where the bus
originated, but it apparently was headed toward Barcelona, 62 miles
south of Figueras.
