<HEAD>Body Lies In Tent Nearly A Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FAYETTEVILLE, Ga. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities believe a waterproof tent
helped preserve the remains of a man who apparently died nearly a
year ago.
   The body was ``completely dried out, leather and bones,'' said
Fayette County Sheriff's Capt. Thomas Nations. ``Evidently, the
tent had stopped the decomposition.''
   The man was tentatively identified as Mark Edmond Whitehead, 36.
Police said the man, formerly of Albany, N.Y., had worked local
construction jobs for several months before telling acquaintances
last year he was moving to a tent.
   The tent and body were found Wednesday by a 17-year-old hunting
squirrels.
   Police said they found a store receipt dated Nov. 1, 1987,
inside the meticulously kept tent. They also found cocaine
paraphernalia.
   The cause of death was not immediately established.
