<HEAD>Pawn Shop Owner Buys His Own, Stolen, Radar Detector</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LINCOLN, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   When pawn shop owner Richard Budig paid a
customer $10 for a radar detector, it crossed his mind that he had
one just like it.
   He was wrong. He used to have one just like it. When he left
work Thursday, he discovered his had been stolen, and the thief
apparently had pawned it right back to him.
   ``In my mind, I said, `I have one just like that in my car,'''
Budig said. ``If I'd have known it was mine, I'd have pulled on the
guy's ears.''
