<2ND_LINE>AM-Three Dead, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0577,0278</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mother And Two Children Found Dead</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS penultimate graf, `Moore declined ...' with 4 grafs to
UPDATE with cause of death and police finding suicide note; Picks
up last graf.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BIRMINGHAM, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man responding to a message recorded
on his office telephone answering machine went home and found his
wife and two children dead.
   Authorities believe Debra Sue Humphrey, 35, distraught about
recent marital problems, killed her 9-year-old son and 5-year-old
daughter before committing suicide Thursday or early Friday.
   William L. Humphrey discovered the bodies Friday morning, said
Lt. Lynn Moore of the Jefferson County Sheriff's Department.
   Humphrey, who apparently had been separated from his wife a
short time, discovered the message early Friday when he arrived at
work.
   The message warned him that something was wrong at home, so he
drove over and found his son, Brandon Michael, and his daughter,
Tiffany Lenor Humphrey, lying dead beside his wife, Moore said.
   Moore declined to disclose the specific content of the recorded
message.
   All three had been shot with a handgun that was recovered at the
home, along with a suicide note, sheriff's Sgt. Eddie White said.
   ``She left a note, at this time we are looking at it as a double
murder and suicide,'' he said.
   White declined to reveal the contents of the note but said it
``basically was just expressing the situation in general. She
regretted doing it and knew it was an immoral act.''
   ``I've never been so shocked in my life,'' said Georgia
Shoemaker, a neighbor. ``I just can't imagine. She seemed so crazy
about those kids.''
</TEXT>
