<2ND_LINE>AM-Strangling Arrests,0466</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three Arrests Follow Widow's Plea For Justice</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police arrested three teen-agers following a
plea for justice from an Israeli immigrant who was slashed and
raped with her teen-age daughter after her husband was strangled.
   ``I have been left with nothing,'' the widow said in an
interview published Friday by Yediot Ahronot, a newspaper in
Israel. ``Now all I want is for them to find my husband's killers,
and to go back to Israel immediately.''
   Police said Saturday they had arrested Angel Diaz, 17, Dutval
Guzman, 15, and Victor Sanchez, 17, all of the Bronx, and charged
them as adults with murder, robbery, burglary and rape. Two other
suspects were being sought, police said.
   ``How, how could God give these people the ability to be such
sadists?'' the widow said in the Yediot Ahronot interview.
   It appeared the suspects killed their former employer in a money
dispute, stole the keys to his apartment, then went there and
attacked his wife and daughter, according to Capt. Thomas Fahey, a
police spokesman. Police declined to elaborate on the dispute.
   The names of the victims were withheld because sex crimes were
involved, said Sgt. Raymond O'Donnell, a police spokesman. However,
he said the 50-year-old man and his family had emigrated here from
Israel about eight years ago.
   The body of the man, a limousine driver and former contractor,
was found slumped in the seat of his car about 3 a.m. Tuesday in
the Bronx. He had been stabbed and strangled.
   About 2 a.m. Tuesday, a gang of youths wearing Halloween masks
entered the man's apartment in Brooklyn and attacked his wife and
teen-age daughter, police said.
   The woman told Yediot Ahronot that she and her daughter were
taken to separate rooms, handcuffed to beds and raped repeatedly.
``Where is the money? Where is your husband?'' they screamed _ but
did not say that her husband had been left for dead.
   The woman said the attackers also threatened to kill her
3-year-old daughter. ``I bit my lips and I knew that if I shouted,
they would kill the baby,'' she said.
   ``They cut them up and threatened them,'' said Judy Mause, a
family friend. ``They were terrified. The daughter is in bad shape.
... She is ruined.''
   The attackers also ransacked and robbed the apartment,
reportedly taking jewelry and $6,000 cash. A 14-year-old son was
away at the time of the attack.
   The man had owned a general contracting business at one point
and had employed Diaz, Guzman and Sanchez, O'Donnell said.
   Diaz was arrested about Friday evening at a Bronx hospital where
his girlfriend was having a baby. The other two arrests were late
Friday and early Saturday, police said.
</TEXT>
