<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Frito-LayRecall     10-22 0171</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Frito-Lay Recall,0175</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Peanut Butter Bars Recalled</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Frito-Lay Inc. is voluntarily recalling 1,576
cases of its Peanut Butter Bars in 22 states west of the
Mississippi River after testing discovered the possibility of
salmonella contamination, the company said Saturday.
   The products have date codes of ``19 Dec 88'' and ``26 Dec 88''
on the front of the package and may have reached store shelves in
the past few days, a company statement said.
   Food and Drug Administration officials have been notified, the
company said.
   The limited recall was described as precautionary and Frito-Lay
said chances of anyone becoming ill from eating the bars is
believed to be remote. Salmonella bacteria have been known to
produce food poisoning and similar intestinal illnesses.
   Consumers were being asked to return the product to Frito-Lay
for a refund.
   The states covered by the recall are: Arizona, Arkansas,
California, Colorado, Idaho, Iowa, Kansas, Louisiana, Minnesota,
Missouri, Montana, Nebraska, Nevada, New Mexico, North Dakota,
Oklahoma, Oregon, South Dakota, Texas, Utah, Washington and Wyoming.
</TEXT>
